		<body xml:lang="en">
			
	<div corresp="#hand01">
	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_000063_0001"/><!--pb/@n='69r'-->
<!-- this is a letter by R S poole including some by DL and John Murray - don't know how to do various hands Poole is hand01-->
<lb/><p rend="right">British Museum</p>
<lb/><p>10th May</p>
<lb/><p>My dear Sir,</p>
<lb/><p>The passage from 
<lb/><persName>Livy</persName> is as follows:</p>
<lb/><p><foreign xml:lang="la">Perfugas, fugitivosque, et 
<lb/>captivos omnes rederrent Romanis, 
<lb/>et naves rostratas, praeter decem 
<lb/>triremes, traderent: elephantosque, 
<lb/>quos haberent domitos neque 
<lb/>domarent alios</foreign> XXX. 37.</p>
<lb/><p>I have kept this note 
<lb/>to insert <persName>D<hi rend="sup">r</hi>. Birch's</persName> reply as 
<lb/>to the Egyptian name of the 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_000063_0002"/><!--pb/@n='69v'-->
<lb/>Island of Elephantine <unclear cert="low">vol</unclear>
<lb/>Philae, but will do so no 
<lb/>longer, but write again.</p>
<lb/><p rend="center"> Pray believe me</p>
<lb/><p rend="center">Yours very faithfully</p>
<lb/><p rend="center"><persName>Reg<hi rend="sup">d</hi>. Stuart Poole</persName></p><!--end of Poole's hand-->
	</div>
	
	<div>
	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_000063_0003"/><!--pb/@n='?'-->
<!--don't know page number-->
<lb/><p><!--this is now DL hand-->Note enclose that 
<lb/>printer may be 
<lb/>correct in 
<lb/>Latin quotation 
<lb/>of footnote 
<lb/>page 600</p><!--end of DL hand-->
	</div>
	<div corresp="#hand02">
<lb/><p><!-- this is now in JM's hand -hand02-->This <hi rend="underline">impossible</hi> to put 
<lb/>this note on Elephants 
<lb/>at page 600 - which is wholly 
<lb/>on Religion. Nowhere in 
<lb/>these 3 sheets can it be 
<lb/><hi rend="underline">suitably</hi> inserted 
<lb/>I would omit it. <unclear cert="medium">J.M</unclear></p>
	</div>

		</body>
